originalText.text: Mr. Schwab is a very bad therapist who doesn’t understand the importance of being empathetic when giving therapy to patients. From my experience, he was very dangerous in the kind of advice that he gave me about medication, specifically advising me to stop taking my psychotropic medication and learning how to will myself to feel better without the medication assistance. Also, he doesn’t believe that mental illness is real... Overall, he was very condescending and insensitive to my feelings. I wouldn’t recommend going to him for therapy.

originalText.text: Very condescending and opinionated. His advice is no better than the sort you might get from a newspaper columnist (and is sometimes comically bad), and he wouldn't let me go into any further detail that might complicate his assessment of my situations.
